    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Tour of Israel, Bottle by Bottle</hl1>
        <hl2 class="online_headline">A Tour of Israel, Bottle by Bottle</hl2>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By HOWARD G. GOLDBERG</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Goldberg, Howard G</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>2007 edition of Rogov's Guide to Israeli Wines, by Daniel Rogov, has just been published (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Admirers of Israel's kosher and nonkosher wines need the 2007 edition of ''Rogov's Guide to Israeli Wines'' (Toby Press, $19.95). Daniel Rogov, Israel's leading critic, rates 1,792 wines through 2005 and 129 wineries.</p>
        <p>His top producers remain Golan Heights Winery, Castel, Flam, Margalit, Yatir, Galil Mountain, Saslove, Amphorae, Recanati and Carmel.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="online_lead_paragraph">
        <p>Admirers of Israel’s kosher and nonkosher wines need the 2007 edition of “Rogov’s Guide to Israeli Wines” (Toby Press, $19.95). Daniel Rogov, Israel’s leading critic, rates 1,792 wines through 2005 and 129 wineries.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Admirers of Israel's kosher and nonkosher wines need the 2007 edition of ''Rogov's Guide to Israeli Wines'' (Toby Press, $19.95). Daniel Rogov, Israel's leading critic, rates 1,792 wines through 2005 and 129 wineries.</p>
        <p>His top producers remain Golan Heights Winery, Castel, Flam, Margalit, Yatir, Galil Mountain, Saslove, Amphorae, Recanati and Carmel.</p>
        <p>''Up and coming'' are Clos de Gat, Chateau Golan, Ella Valley, Sea Horse, Carmei Yosef, Alexander, Gustavo &amp; Jo, Bazelet ha Golan, Orna Chillag and La Terra Promessa.</p>
        <p>HOWARD G. GOLDBERG</p>
        <p>WINE UNDER $20</p>
      </block>
